      "locked": false,
      "text": "- signals - write/read (get with (), set(x), update(x => x ))\n- computed - read only - \"watches\" any signals inside the computed, and returns a new value if those signals change \n- effect - \"side effect\" - do this work when the signals \"captured\" in that effect change.\n    - can only be used in an \"injection context\" - that is usually a constructor in a component (or class), but there are\n      others - as you'll see.\n    - pretty much makes OnInit unneeded - this is the replacement for it (hint, effect can run in any injection context)\n- takes an optional argument that is a function that will be called when the effect is destroyed.\n- linkedSignal - computed and a signal got married. \n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- signals - write/read (get with (), set(x), update(x => x ))\n- computed - read only - \"watches\" any signals inside the computed, and returns a new value if those signals change \n- effect - \"side effect\" - do this work when the signals \"captured\" in that effect change.\n    - can only be used in an \"injection context\" - that is usually a constructor in a component (or class), but there are\n      others - as you'll see.\n    - pretty much makes OnInit unneeded - this is the replacement for it (hint, effect can run in any injection context)\n- takes an optional argument that is a function that will be called when the effect is destroyed.\n- linkedSignal - computed and a signal got married. \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
